  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Due to their immunosuppressive therapy, solid-organ transplant (SOT) recipients bear a 10 to
      100 times higher risk of human papillomavirus (HPV)-associated malignancies than healthy
      individuals. The objectives of this observational, non-interventional multi-national,
      multi-centre research project are to gain an insight into current HPV vaccination strategies
      and to investigate the immune response to different routinely administered HPV vaccines in
      European paediatric SOT candidates and immunocompromised transplant recipients, enabling
      patients at risk of vaccination failure to be identified.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
